hints.description: This technology giant designs, develops, and sells consumer electronics, computer software, and online services. Their product line includes computers, wearables, and a variety of services like cloud storage and digital content distribution. Founded by Steve Jobs, Steve Wozniak, and Ronald Wayne, the company is renowned for its innovative design and marketing strategies.
hints.funFact1: Before becoming a tech behemoth, the company was initially focused on building and selling handcrafted computers for hobbyists, and even briefly explored the idea of producing pinball machines.
hints.funFact2: The first version of the Macintosh operating system, released in 1984, was largely developed by a small team of employees working in a secret location nicknamed "The Garage"  a far cry from their current sprawling campuses.
